ding yoga posture that strengthens the core and lower body.";i:1;s:112:"In this pose the arms extend upward alongside the ears while the knees bend as if sitting on an imaginary chair.";i:2;s:110:"This is an important pose in yoga for energizing the entire body and promoting creativity and mental strength.";i:3;s:40:"Chair pose is also known as fierce pose.";i:4;s:135:"Utkatasanas name comes from the Sanskrit utkata which means fierce proud high haughty superior immense large difficultyou get the idea.";i:5;s:109:"This pose is often called chair pose in English because it looks as if you are sitting in an invisible chair.";i:6;s:26:"But this is no easy chair.";i:7;s:23:"Its more like a throne.";i:8;s:52:"The Origin and Meaning of Utkatasana The Chair Pose.";i:9;s:73:"Utkata in Sanskrit has many meanings including powerful proud and fierce.";i:10;s:122:"The English name of this posture simply stems from the appearance of sitting in a chair an imaginary one in this instance.";i:11;s:71:"The asana actually has its origin in Hindu mythology specifically from.";i:12;s:98:"This pose is mainly referred to as the Fierce Pose where Utkata means violent or fierce or severe.";i:13;s:117:"This pose is also called the Chair pose just because the posture resembles like one is sitting on an invisible chair.";i:14;s:66:"This pose is one of the first pose in the Sun Salutation B series.";i:15;s:132:"It needs ample strength with the quadricep muscles to help your hips get the right support and give the knees a comfort to hold the.";i:16;s:95:"Chair pose is a standing squat that let upper and lower body muscles strengthen simultaneously.";i:17;s:96:"While holding this pose for a while you will feel an intense stretch in the shoulder upper back.";i:18;s:73:"On regular practice your quadriceps gluteus calves ankles get strengthen.";i:19;s:117:"Utkatasana or the Chair Pose comes from the Sanskrit words Utkata meaning fierce or intense and asana meaning a pose.";i:20;s:130:"Utkatasana is 